tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE swimmer_feedback (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  swimmer_id INT NOT NULL,
  coach_evaluation TEXT,
  judge_evaluation TEXT,
  rating FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceEvaluation (
    EvaluationID INT,
    SwimmerID INT,
    JudgeID INT,
    Rating INT,
    Comments TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Swimmers (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    coach_feedback TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Evaluations (
    evaluation_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    swimmer_id INT NOT NULL,
    coach_id INT NOT NULL,
    judge_id INT NOT NULL,
    feedback TEXT,
    score INT
);
CREATE TABLE Swimmers(id INT, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), level VARCHAR(20));
CREATE TABLE Coaches(id INT, name VARCHAR(50), experience_years INT, specialty VARCHAR(50), certification VARCHAR(50));
CREATE TABLE Judges(id INT, name VARCHAR(50), affiliation VARCHAR(100));
CREATE TABLE Feedback(id INT, swimmer_id INT, coach_id INT, judge_id INT, overall_score INT, comments TEXT, date DATE);
CREATE TABLE PerformanceEvaluations(id INT, swimmer_id INT, coach_id INT, judge_id INT, performance_score INT, comments TEXT, date DATE);
